# Smart Health Bracelet Use Cases

## 1. Real-Time Health Monitoring
- **Description**: Users receive continuous feedback on vital health metrics such as heart rate, blood oxygen levels, blood pressure, and body temperature.
- **Requirement**: The system must display real-time data through an interactive interface.

## 2. Alert System
- **Description**: The bracelet sends immediate alerts for abnormal readings, prompting users to take timely action.
- **Requirement**: The system must have the capability to trigger notifications for health metrics that fall outside of predefined thresholds.

## 3. Personalized Health Guidance
- **Description**: The system analyzes user data trends to provide tailored health advice, enabling informed lifestyle choices.
- **Requirement**: The processing unit must be able to generate health recommendations based on the analysis of historical data.

## 4. Goal Setting and Tracking
- **Description**: Users can set specific health goals (e.g., target heart rate) and monitor their progress visually.
- **Requirement**: The system must allow users to input and track health goals within the application.

## 5. Data Sharing with Healthcare Providers
- **Description**: Users can share their health data with medical professionals for improved consultations.
- **Requirement**: The system must provide a secure method for exporting health data to healthcare providers.

## 6. Community Engagement
- **Description**: Users can connect with others on similar health journeys, sharing experiences and motivating each other.
- **Requirement**: The application must include features for community interaction, such as forums or group challenges.
